text:
Kate Osborne is a British Labour Party politician. She has been the Member of Parliament (MP) for Jarrow since the 2019 general election.
Osborne is known for being a trade union and a LGBT+ activist and campaigner. Osborne is married to Pamela Brooks-Osborn.
In March 2020, Osborne became the second British Member of Parliament to test positive for Coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19), after Nadine Dorries.
